content.description: Short but steep problem left of the Red Kelly Wall. Starts left of a small "cave". Start low on good pockets, climb out steep buldge, to a Kelly Canyon style topout.
content.location: Left most feature. Left of Red Kelly Wall.

content.description: Red Kelly is the better of the lines on the Red Kelly Wall. Climbs up the steepest cleanest face on the right side of the wall. Start on neat horizontal ledges and make big moves to decent holds out steep face. Climb through large huecos near top. Skirt carefully through foliage to top. Descend off left.
content.location: Right side of Red Kelly Wall. Look for neat huecos near the top.

content.description: The Lesser Key climbs the face to the right of Red Kelly. Start on the same horizontal ledge found on Red Kelly. Climb out steep face on red, sandy holds. Fun movement on cool holds. Top out is dirty.
content.location: Right side of Red Kelly Wall.

content.description: FireStar climbs the left most steep arete on The Red Kelly Wall. Start Low move through series of hard moves to a dirty topout.
content.location: Left most steep arete on The Red Kelly Wall.

content.description: Economy Bubble climbs the arete/face to the left of the crack that splits the Red Kelly Wall. Start low on small holds, make hard moves between small holds on the arete. Topout "not recommended".
content.location: Left of crack on Red Kelly Wall.

content.description:
Red Kelly Wall is the furthest wall in from Pumphouse Wash. Red colored and overhung the Red Kelly Wall receives the most amount of shade. Worth the walk for seclusion and unique climbing. 

  Beware of Poison Ivy during Summer months!
